Hy, ich nehme das Medi auch seit November. Bevor ich damit begonnen habe, hätte ich nicht gedacht wieder ein halbwegs normales Leben zu führen. Schon nach den ersten Spritzen merkte ich deutliche Verbesserung, was auch zur einer bedeutenden Steigerung meiner Lebensqualität führte :-) Klar können die Meinungen sehr unterschiedlich sein und sicherlich habe auch ich Nebenwirkungen. Aber es ist auch sehr abzuwägen, wie ging es mir vorher? Ich war echt am Ende und war auch nicht mehr arbeitsfähig. Vollgepumpt mit sämtlichen anderen Medis die bei weitem schädigender für meinen Körper waren. Und was sind Nebenwirkungen .... eigentlich sind die Beschwerden weshalb man ja Humira bekommt genauso wenn eben nicht noch schlimmer. Ich freu mich auch jemanden gefunden zu haben, der Humira nimmt, vielleicht kann man sich ja mal ein bisschen austauschen und auch mal Tipps geben und bekommen um dann noch besser mit den Nebenwirkungen klarzukommen. Auch muss ich sagen, gerade mit meinem Beschwerdebild stand ich oft alleine und mit Unverständnis da. Von mir bekommt Humira auf jeden Fall ein Like!

I have been on Humira for many years (before that remicade) and now after going on medicare can not afford my pens.  Last year the co-pay was $1500 for 6 pens and 1/1/17 the co-pay is $3000.  Not bad at $500/pen.  I guess I am paying for all those ads on TV.  Never ceases to amaze me how up until social security I had the $5 OPUS card and went on Medicare and not have to pay $3000  I have written to the Presiden, Vice President and head of marketing and all letters returned.  Try to find a contact number or address and I guarantee you it is the best well kept secret.  I won't die from Crohn's but the complications will definitely be my demise.  Any answers, anyone.
The Medactiv iCool Prestige bag has now given me the confidence to travel and go on holidays. Travelling with Humira is always unsettling on long distance travel.

Woran erkenne ich ECHTES Henna???

Es wird erst nach einigen Tagen dunkel.

Wer bereits einmal echte frische Hennablätter zum Färben verwendet hat (traditionelle Art) weiß, dass das Henna erst nach ein bis zwei Tagen dunkel wird. Wie können dann angeblich ECHTE natürliche HENNATUBEN, die man auf dem Markt bekommt, bereits innerhalb von einigen Stunden dunkel werden, wenn es die Blätter, woraus Henna gewonnen wird, nicht schaffen???

So arbeitet echtes Naturhenna.

Bild links nach einem Tag.
Bild rechts nach drei Tagen.

posts.message: Just wanted to touch base with everyone. Not much has changed in the way of remission of my crohn's. I have however been accepted in to a group called Prometheus that helps gets the medicine awaiting results from blood tests I may have access to low cost medicine in the near future. Things are going great with my wife and son. He is growing like a tree.

Hi everyone I just wanted to thanks you for continued support. Thanks to you guys for being so generous and taking time to help this person in need. I love you all. Thanks again for helping me find the light in all the darkness

Just sharing this will raise awareness and help the cause. With remission of crohn's it would dramaticly increase the quality of life . I would love to spend more time with my family. I am tired of always feeling miserable , always staying behind, always waiting on it to get better.
I would like to thank you landing on my page. I have a favor to ask you. Would you share my page at least once? Just one share per person greatly increases the chance of a donor.

posts.message:
HUMIRA is a prescription medicine used:
•To reduce the signs and symptoms of: ◦Moderate to severe rheumatoid arthritis (RA) in adults. HUMIRA can be used alone, with methotrexate, or with certain other medicines. HUMIRA may prevent further damage to your bones and joints and may help your ability to perform daily activities.
◦Moderate to severe polyarticular juvenile idiopathic arthritis (JIA) in children 2 years of age and older. HUMIRA can be used alone, with methotrexate, or with certain other medicines.
◦Psoriatic arthritis (PsA) in adults. HUMIRA can be used alone or with certain other medicines. HUMIRA may prevent further damage to your bones and joints and may help your ability to perform daily activities.
◦Ankylosing spondylitis (AS) in adults.
◦Moderate to severe Crohn's disease (CD) and to achieve and maintain clinical remission in adults who have not responded well to conventional treatments. HUMIRA is also used to reduce signs and symptoms and to achieve clinical remission in these adults who have lost response to or are unable to tolerate infliximab.
◦Moderate to severe Crohn's disease (CD) and to achieve and maintain clinical remission in children 6 years of age and older when certain other treatments have not worked well enough.

•In adults, to help get moderate to severe ulcerative colitis (UC) under control (induce remission) and keep it under control (sustain remission) when certain other medicines have not worked well enough. It is not known if HUMIRA is effective in people who stopped responding to or could not tolerate anti-TNF medicines.
•To treat moderate to severe chronic plaque psoriasis (Ps) in adults who are ready for systemic therapy or phototherapy, and are under the care of a doctor who will decide if other systemic therapies are less appropriate.
